The Telegraph - Calcutta
 3-day exhibition in Delhi
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: An exhibition of the 1952 Olympics, to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Helsinki Games, will be held from Tuesday to Thursday at the capitals National Stadium. This is according to a Consulate of Finland press release. The exhibition, being organised by the Embassy of Finland, New Delhi, will highlight Indian participation at the 15th Olympic Games. Each participant will be presented a special medal. The exhibition, to be inaugurated at 11 am on Tuesday, will be open to the general public on all three days.  Copyright 
